{"id": "23215", "post": "<div class=\"post-23215 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-tutorials tag-crontab tag-rundeck tag-take-control-of-your-jobs tag-tutorial\" id=\"post-23215\"><h2 class=\"storytitle\"><a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/blog/take-control-of-your-jobs-with-rundeck/\" rel=\"bookmark\">Take Control of Your Cron Jobs With Rundeck</a></h2><div class=\"meta\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" data-src=\"/media/icons/tag_green.png\" alt=\"Tags: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/crontab/\" rel=\"tag\">crontab</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/rundeck/\" rel=\"tag\">rundeck</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/take-control-of-your-jobs/\" rel=\"tag\">take control of your jobs</a>, <a href=\"https://lowendbox.com/tag/tutorial/\" rel=\"tag\">tutorial</a> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/media/icons/calendar.png\" alt=\"Date/Time: \" class=\"litespeed-loaded\" data-was-processed=\"true\"> August 29, 2020 @ 7:04 am, by raindog308</div><div class=\"storycontent tablelook\"><p><a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-logo.gif.webp\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"screenshot litespeed-loaded\" title=\"Take Control of your Jobs with Rundeck\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-logo.gif.webp\" alt=\"Take Control of your Jobs with Rundeck\" width=\"300\" height=\"244\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></a></p><p>In this tutorial, we\u2019ll show you how to setup and get started with Rundeck, a free (as in beer) job control solution.</p><h1>Why Rundeck?</h1><p>For some simple needs, crontab suffices.&nbsp; If you have a job you want to run at 1am, you stick it in crontab (or use atd), it runs, and you\u2019re happy.</p><p>But what if you have more complex needs?&nbsp; For example, \u201cbackup these databases, and if that succeeds, tarball this source code, then git pull, then restart these systems, then run these maintenance jobs\u2026\u201d&nbsp; You could do that all as different cron jobs, but you lose the ability to set dependencies.&nbsp; You could write a mother script to call many scripts, but then you lose modularity and create a brittle sprawl.&nbsp; And what if you want to manage jobs across many servers?&nbsp; &nbsp;What if the results of jobs on some drive what happens on others?&nbsp; And what if you want to make jobs easy to run one-off \u2013 perhaps even allowing end-users to do so without needing to give them all the keys to the kingdom?</p><p>This type of complex job management was for years the domain of stratospherically expensive job enterprise control solutions.&nbsp; Rundeck is a free product that gives you tremendous power in managing systems.</p><p>Personally, I have a home Rundeck server that controls backups on all my home systems and VPSes, housekeeping jobs, seedbox maintenance and conversion jobs, rotating pictures on our digital photo frame, etc.</p><p><span id=\"more-23215\"></span></p><h1>Setting Up Rundeck</h1><p>In this tutorial, I\u2019ll create a Rundeck server (master.lowend.party) and a single node (slave.lowend.party).&nbsp; Rundeck can scale to control hundreds (perhaps thousands) of nodes, but the principles are the same.</p><p>In this case, I\u2019m using a Debian 9 VPS with 4GB of RAM for my master, and a Debian 10 VPS with 1GB of RAM for the salve.&nbsp; The reason for Debian 9 on the master is that Rundeck requires OpenJDK 8, which is easily installable on Debian 9.&nbsp; Support for OpenJDK 11 is coming but at the moment, JDK 8 is required.</p><p>After imaging the master, I installed some required packages:</p><pre>apt-get install openjdk-8-jre-headless mariadb-server gnupg2 apt-transport-https</pre><p>After installing MariaDB, I secured it.</p><pre>root@master:~# mysql_secure_installation\n\nNOTE: RUNNING ALL PARTS OF THIS SCRIPT IS RECOMMENDED FOR ALL MariaDB\nSERVERS IN PRODUCTION USE! PLEASE READ EACH STEP CAREFULLY!\n\nIn order to log into MariaDB to secure it, we'll need the current\npassword for the root user. If you've just installed MariaDB, and\nyou haven't set the root password yet, the password will be blank,\nso you should just press enter here.\n\nEnter current password for root (enter for none):\nOK, successfully used password, moving on...\n\nSetting the root password ensures that nobody can log into the MariaDB\nroot user without the proper authorisation.\n\nSet root password? [Y/n] y\nNew password:\nRe-enter new password:\nPassword updated successfully!\nReloading privilege tables..\n... Success!\n\nBy default, a MariaDB installation has an anonymous user, allowing anyone\nto log into MariaDB without having to have a user account created for\nthem. This is intended only for testing, and to make the installation\ngo a bit smoother. You should remove them before moving into a\nproduction environment.\n\nRemove anonymous users? [Y/n] y\n... Success!\n\nNormally, root should only be allowed to connect from 'localhost'. This\nensures that someone cannot guess at the root password from the network.\n\nDisallow root login remotely? [Y/n] y\n... Success!\n\nBy default, MariaDB comes with a database named 'test' that anyone can\naccess. This is also intended only for testing, and should be removed\nbefore moving into a production environment.\n\nRemove test database and access to it? [Y/n] y\n- Dropping test database...\n... Success!\n- Removing privileges on test database...\n... Success!\n\nReloading the privilege tables will ensure that all changes made so far\nwill take effect immediately.\n\nReload privilege tables now? [Y/n] y\n... Success!\n\nCleaning up...\n\nAll done! If you've completed all of the above steps, your MariaDB\ninstallation should now be secure.\n\nThanks for using MariaDB!</pre><p>Now we\u2019ll create a database for Rundeck.</p><pre>root@master:/etc/rundeck# mysql\nWelcome to the MariaDB monitor. Commands end with ; or \\g.\nYour MariaDB connection id is 55\nServer version: 10.3.22-MariaDB-0+deb10u1 Debian 10\n\nCopyright (c) 2000, 2018, Oracle, MariaDB Corporation Ab and others.\n\nType 'help;' or '\\h' for help. Type '\\c' to clear the current input statement.\n\nMariaDB [(none)]&gt; create database rundeck;\nQuery OK, 1 row affected (0.000 sec)\n\nMariaDB [(none)]&gt; grant ALL on rundeck.* to 'rundeckuser'@'localhost' identified by 'rundeckpassword';\nQuery OK, 0 rows affected (0.000 sec)\n\nMariaDB [(none)]&gt; flush privileges;\nQuery OK, 0 rows affected (0.000 sec)\n\nMariaDB [(none)]&gt; Bye</pre><p>Now let\u2019s install Rundeck itself.</p><pre>echo \"deb https://rundeck.bintray.com/rundeck-deb /\" &gt; /etc/apt/sources.list.d/rundeck.list\ncurl 'https://bintray.com/user/downloadSubjectPublicKey?username=bintray' | apt-key add -\napt-get update\napt-get install rundeck</pre><p>Before we startup Rundeck, we want to make some configuration changes.&nbsp; All of Rundeck\u2019s configuration is in /etc/rundeck.</p><p>Modify framework.properties:</p><pre>framework.server.name = master.lowend.party\nframework.server.hostname = master.lowend.party\nframework.server.port = 4440\nframework.server.url = http://master.lowend.party:4440</pre><p>Modify rundeck-config.properties to change from using h2 (a slow internal database only suitable for testing) to the MariaDB database we set up:</p><pre>grails.serverURL=http://master.lowend.party:4440</pre><pre>#dataSource.url = jdbc:h2:file:/var/lib/rundeck/data/rundeckdb;MVCC=true\ndataSource.url = jdbc:mysql://localhost/rundeck?autoReconnect=true&amp;useSSL=false\ndataSource.username=rundeckuser\ndataSource.password=rundeckpassword\ndataSource.driverClassName=com.mysql.jdbc.Driver</pre><p>Modify realm.properties to set a password fo the \u2018admin\u2019 account.&nbsp; The default password is \u2018admin\u2019.&nbsp; Change it to something better:</p><pre>admin:complex-password,user,admin,architect,deploy,build</pre><p>Now start Rundeck:</p><pre>systemctl start rundeckd</pre><p>Now you can see Rundeck running (via ps -ef):</p><pre>rundeck 6810 1 99 12:44 ? 00:00:21 java -Drundeck.jaaslogin=true -Djava.security.auth.login.config</pre><p>It may take Rundeck a few moments to startup.&nbsp; If you look at /var/log/rundeck/service.log you\u2019ll see this message towards the end that Rundeck is ready:</p><pre>[2020-05-19 12:47:46.891] INFO BootStrap --- [ main] Rundeck startup finished in 2202ms</pre><p>Rundeck runs on port 4440, so I surfed to master.lowend.party:4440.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI0NTAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzgzIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgNDUwIDM4MyI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23220\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-1-login.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"450\" height=\"383\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-1-login.png.webp 450w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-1-login-300x255.png.webp 300w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px\"></p><p>Login as admin with the password you set in realm.properties above.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzg5IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDM4OSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23221\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-2-new-project.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"389\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-2-new-project.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-2-new-project-300x146.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-2-new-project-768x373.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Now click New Project.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzY2IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDM2NiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23222\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-3-create-new-project.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"366\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-3-create-new-project.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-3-create-new-project-300x137.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-3-create-new-project-768x351.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Click Create.&nbsp; Now in the left menu bar, expand Project Settings and click Edit Nodes.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iODE0IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDgxNCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23223\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-4-edit-nodes.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"814\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-4-edit-nodes.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-4-edit-nodes-295x300.png.webp 295w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-4-edit-nodes-768x781.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>We now need to setup our list of nodes.&nbsp; We need a read from a \u201csource\u201d.&nbsp; This could be something exotic like the output from a giant enterprise database system, Ansible, a URL, etc.&nbsp; But for this tutorial, we\u2019ll read from a file.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNzAxIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDcwMSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23224\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-5-add-new-source.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"701\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-5-add-new-source.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-5-add-new-source-300x263.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-5-add-new-source-768x673.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Click File.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNTkwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDU5MCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23225\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-6-resourceyaml.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"590\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-6-resourceyaml.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-6-resourceyaml-300x221.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-6-resourceyaml-768x566.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>We\u2019ll use YAML.&nbsp; We\u2019re going to let Rundeck generate a new file for us.&nbsp; Fill out the boxes as shown.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzY3IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDM2NyI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23226\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-7-resourceyaml-setup.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"367\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-7-resourceyaml-setup.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-7-resourceyaml-setup-300x138.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-7-resourceyaml-setup-768x352.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Now click save.&nbsp; On master, in /var/lib/rundeck/data, this file now exists:</p><p class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">root@master:/var/lib/rundeck/data# cat nodes.yaml </span></p><pre class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">master.lowend.party:</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>nodename: master.lowend.party</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>hostname: master.lowend.party</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>osVersion: 4.9.0-12-amd64</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>osFamily: unix</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>osArch: amd64</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>description: Rundeck server node</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>osName: Linux</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>username: rundeck</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>tags: ''</span></pre><p>I added a new entry for slave:</p><pre class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">master.lowend.party:</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>nodename: master.lowend.party</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>hostname: master.lowend.party</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>osVersion: 4.9.0-12-amd64</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>osFamily: unix</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>osArch: amd64</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>description: Rundeck server node</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>osName: Linux</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>username: rundeck</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>tags: ''</span>\n<span class=\"s1\">slave.lowend.party:</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>nodename: slave.lowend.party</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>hostname: slave.lowend.party</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>osVersion: 4.9.0-12-amd64</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>osFamily: unix</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>osArch: amd64</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>description: Rundeck slave node</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>osName: Linux</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>username: rundeck</span>\n<span class=\"s1\"><span class=\"Apple-converted-space\">&nbsp; </span>tags: ''</span></pre><p>Now let\u2019s setup SSH keys.&nbsp; Once again select Edit Configuration on Project Settings.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIyMTAiIGhlaWdodD0iNTc2IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMjEwIDU3NiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23227\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-8-edit-config.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"210\" height=\"576\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-8-edit-config.png.webp 210w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-8-edit-config-109x300.png.webp 109w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 210px) 100vw, 210px\"></p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzQ5IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDM0OSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23228\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-9-default-file-exec.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"349\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-9-default-file-exec.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-9-default-file-exec-300x131.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-9-default-file-exec-768x335.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Click Default Node Executor.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNjEzIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDYxMyI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23230\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-10-ssh-path.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"613\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-10-ssh-path.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-10-ssh-path-300x230.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-10-ssh-path-768x588.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>You\u2019ll see that SSH is the default way that Rundeck will connect to systems and run jobs.&nbsp; Let\u2019s use the name already in use and create a passwordless SSH key:</p><pre>root@master:/var/lib/rundeck# ssh-keygen -f /var/lib/rundeck/.ssh/id_rsa\nGenerating public/private rsa key pair.\nEnter passphrase (empty for no passphrase):\nEnter same passphrase again:\nYour identification has been saved in /var/lib/rundeck/.ssh/id_rsa.\nYour public key has been saved in /var/lib/rundeck/.ssh/id_rsa.pub.\nThe key fingerprint is:\nSHA256:jKEPwDsvSDZ7WB1Sc9tRiBFgC+JI3c6IO1xhriTL1NE root@master.lowend.party\nThe key's randomart image is:\n+---[RSA 2048]----+\n| o..o=.++.o. |\n|+..=+E+.o.. |\n|..B.*o.. . |\n|.+ Bo+.+ |\n|*=*.o.. S |\n|+B=o o |\n|.oo.. . |\n| .. |\n| |\n+----[SHA256]-----+\nroot@master:/var/lib/rundeck# chown rundeck:rundeck /var/lib/rundeck/.ssh/id*</pre><h1>Setting Up Slave</h1><p>On the slave server, I created rundeck account and placed the id_rsa.pub ssh key in rundeck\u2019s authorized_keys.&nbsp; I also allowed the rundeck user to execute jobs as root by placing a file in /etc/sudoers.d/rundeck with these contents:</p><pre class=\"p1\"><span class=\"s1\">rundeck ALL=(ALL:ALL) NOPASSWD: ALL</span></pre><p>Now I\u2019ve created a job to run:</p><pre>root@slave:/etc/sudoers.d# cat /usr/local/bin/maintenance.sh\n#!/bin/bash\n\napt-get update\napt-get -y upgrade</pre><h1>Creating a Job</h1><p>Back in the Rundeck interface, click Jobs.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjY1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDI2NSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23229\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-10-create-job.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"265\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-10-create-job.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-10-create-job-300x99.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-10-create-job-768x254.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Click \u201cJob Actions\u201d, and then click \u201cNew Job\u201d.&nbsp; Fill out the form with a suitable name and description.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNjk4IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDY5OCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23246\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-10a-create-job.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"698\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-10a-create-job.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-10a-create-job-300x262.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-10a-create-job-768x670.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Now click Workflow.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNDQwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDQ0MCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23232\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-12-workflow.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"440\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-12-workflow.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-12-workflow-300x165.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-12-workflow-768x422.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Click Add Step.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNTI4IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDUyOCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23233\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-13-command.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"528\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-13-command.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-13-command-300x198.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-13-command-768x507.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Select Command.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTkwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDE5MCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23234\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-14-command-spec.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"190\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-14-command-spec.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-14-command-spec-300x71.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-14-command-spec-768x182.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Now click Save, then click Nodes.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzIyIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDMyMiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23235\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-15-nodes.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"322\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-15-nodes.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-15-nodes-300x121.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-15-nodes-768x309.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Select Dispatch to Nodes.&nbsp; Under Node Filter, I\u2019ve entered the node name.&nbsp; If you had nodes in a specific format, you could use wildcards (e.g., prod*, etc.), list nodes, or use * for all nodes.</p><p>You can also configure instructions on how to handle failed nodes:</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTA0IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDEwNCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23236\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-16-continue-after-fail.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"104\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-16-continue-after-fail.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-16-continue-after-fail-300x39.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-16-continue-after-fail-768x100.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Now save the job definition.&nbsp; On the main job page, select the job.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI2NTQiIGhlaWdodD0iODYiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCA2NTQgODYiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIGZpbGw9IiNjZmQ0ZGIiLz48L3N2Zz4=\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23248\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-run-job-1.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"654\" height=\"86\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-run-job-1.png 654w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-run-job-1-300x39.png.webp 300w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 654px) 100vw, 654px\"></p><p>And then Run Job Now:</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjYwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDI2MCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23249\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-run-job-2.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"260\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-run-job-2.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-run-job-2-300x98.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-run-job-2-768x250.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>In the subsequent window, you\u2019ll see the job\u2019s result:</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNjQiIHZpZXdCb3g9IjAgMCA4MDAgNjQiPjxyZWN0IHdpZHRoPSIxMDAlIiBoZWlnaHQ9IjEwMCUiIGZpbGw9IiNjZmQ0ZGIiLz48L3N2Zz4=\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23237\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-17-all-steps-ok.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"64\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-17-all-steps-ok.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-17-all-steps-ok-300x24.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-17-all-steps-ok-768x61.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><h1>Automating Job Execution</h1><p>Let\u2019s set the job to run without need for manual execution.</p><p>On the project\u2019s jobs page, select Actions and then Edit This Job.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjY2IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDI2NiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23238\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-18-edit-job.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"266\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-18-edit-job.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-18-edit-job-300x100.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-18-edit-job-768x255.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Click Schedule.&nbsp; The default \u201csimple scheduler\u201d will appear:</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNDY3IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDQ2NyI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23239\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-19-schedule-simple.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"467\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-19-schedule-simple.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-19-schedule-simple-300x175.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-19-schedule-simple-768x448.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>This is sufficient for most scheduling, but if you need more advanced options, you can switch to Crontab scheduling by clicking \u201cCrontab\u201d:</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNjY1IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDY2NSI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23240\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-20-schedule-complex.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"665\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-20-schedule-complex.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-20-schedule-complex-300x249.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-20-schedule-complex-768x638.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>We can also setup notifications.&nbsp; For various states, such as job success or job failure, Rundeck can send an email or POST to a web hook (see the documentation for details).&nbsp; Here I will configure the job to email me if it fails.&nbsp; Note that I\u2019m using one of the available Rundeck variables (${job_name}) so I don\u2019t have to type the job name.&nbsp; These variables are covered in the documentation.</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzAyIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDMwMiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23241\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-21-notifications.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"302\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-21-notifications.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-21-notifications-300x113.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-21-notifications-768x290.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><h1>Multi-Step Jobs</h1><p>Let\u2019s make our job a bit more complicated by linking several steps together.</p><p>On the slave, I\u2019ve created a script to do MariaDB backups.&nbsp; I also want to clean out old backups as well.&nbsp; For that, I will use an Inline Script as opposed to a Command.&nbsp; Here\u2019s how my workflow looks now:</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMzA3IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDMwNyI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23251\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-multi.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"307\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-multi.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-multi-300x115.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-multi-768x295.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><p>Now when I execute the job, I see all steps firing sequentially:</p><p><img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTQ2IiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDE0NiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23243\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-23-steps-ok.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"146\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-23-steps-ok.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-23-steps-ok-300x55.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-23-steps-ok-768x140.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"> <img data-lazyloaded=\"1\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMjcyIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgODAwIDI3MiI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-23244\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-24-details.png.webp\" alt=\"\" width=\"800\" height=\"272\" data-srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-24-details.png.webp 800w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-24-details-300x102.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/rundeck-24-details-768x261.png.webp 768w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></p><h1>Learning More</h1><p>We\u2019ve barely scratched the surface of Rundeck\u2019s capabilities.&nbsp; To learn more, visit <a href=\"https://www.rundeck.com/\">Rundeck.com</a> and peruse the <a href=\"https://docs.rundeck.com/docs/\">documentation</a>.</p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-content dpsp-has-button-icon-animation\"><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Ftake-control-of-your-jobs-with-rundeck%2F&amp;t=Take%20Control%20of%20Your%20Cron%20Jobs%20With%20Rundeck\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp-facebook dpsp-no-label 